SOTO: Today is a beginning, not just an ending, and the experiences and memories you have created of the last few years will be of service to you long after you leave here.
SOTO: Always remember you have an obligation to help others gain the same joys and face the same challenges that you did.
SOTO: As caterpillars return to their roosting places as butterflies, it will always be important to remember where you came from and who raised you.
SOTO: Confidence alone doesn’t translate into preparation.
SOTO: The ‘uh-oh’ moments are worth cherishing just as much as ‘ah-ha’ moments: Mistakes, failures, embarrassments and disappointments are a necessary component of growing wise.
SOTO: We can learn more from our not-so-good experiences than we can learn from our good ones.